            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> When a window or tabpage has a local CWD, it's not easy to reset to the \"parent scope\" CWD. (Or is this possible already?)\n\n```vimscript\n\" has run :tcd.\n:exe 'cd' getcwd(-1,-1)\n\n\" has run :lcd.\n:exe 'tcd' getcwd(-1,0)\n```\n\nor am I missing something?\n\nRegarding `!`, It's reasonable for me that `set tgc!` as a toggle, but that `:tcd!` sounds like \"Well, `:tcd` will fail sometimes, so here I bang(`!`) it to ensure that it'll work anyway.\"\n\nEdit: update script.",
