        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I agree that my part doesn't look very ergonomic. (but personally, I'm fine typing it)\n\nRegarding the proposed UI, I would argue that the default is a bit weird:\n\n> :tcd! (bang) clears the tab-local CWD, but not the window-local CWD (if any)?\n\nMy arguments:\n\n1. Before this `:tcd!`, there seems to be no ergonomic way of \"clear tab-local CWD, but keep the window-local one\" completely in the command line.\n2. By point 1., I would assume that only a very small group of people need that. Thus a bad default.\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
